page_4_img_3.png.full_caption: Fig. 3  Differential spectroelectrochemistry. (a) and (b) Differential absorption spectra of PBBT-H (a) and PBBT-Me (b). (c) Differential absorption spectra of PBBT-H (c) and PBBT-Me (d) at select wavelengths. page_6_img_1.png.full_caption: Fig. 5 OECT-based inverters. (a) and (b) Typical voltage transfer characteristics (VTC) of the inverters at various supply voltages (from 0.2 to 0.7 V). page_6_img_3.png.title: Stable organic electrochemical neurons based on p-type and n-type ladder polymers
page_6_img_3.png.full_caption: Fig. 6 Organic electrochemical neurons based on PBBT-Me and BBL. (a) Schematic of the leaky-integrate-and-fire (LIF) type spiking neuron, comprising both p-type and n-type accumulation-mode OECTs. (b) Typical spiking behaviors of a LIF-neuron based on PBBT-Me and BBL, gated using Ag/AgCl and working at In = 2 μA in 0.1 M NaCl aqueous solution. (c) Spiking frequency and Vfire,max of the LIF-neuron at different In. (d) Spiking patterns at In = 2 μA for 0 h, 3 h, and 6.5 h. (e) Spiking frequencies of the LIF-neuron change over time at In = 0.25 μA, 1 μA, 6 μA during 6.5 h of continuous operation. (f) Evolution of the Vfire,max over time at In = 0.25 μA, 1 μA, 6 μA during 6.5 h of continuous operation.
